WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:00:25.775 --> 00:00:27.277
Well then, let's get going.

00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:49.299
Temperatures are unusually high, huh?

00:00:51.217 --> 00:00:52.551
But…

00:00:52.552 --> 00:00:55.805
it seems our funds are getting low.

00:00:57.098 --> 00:01:01.102
We will have to find work
when we get to the next town.

00:01:01.686 --> 00:01:04.355
You're already thinking that far, Fern?

00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:07.859
It's important. Master Stark,

00:01:08.568 --> 00:01:11.361
you have to think
a few steps ahead at all times,

00:01:11.362 --> 00:01:13.114
or you can't travel very long.

00:01:14.115 --> 00:01:15.575
I guess you're right.

00:01:17.202 --> 00:01:19.119
Work, huh?

00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:21.206
Hopefully they have
some nice job requests.

00:01:23.458 --> 00:01:24.501
{\an8}Oh?

00:01:25.585 --> 00:01:26.669
It's kind of…

00:01:29.255 --> 00:01:32.007
{\an8}Thank you very much for giving us a ride.

00:01:32.008 --> 00:01:36.011
{\an8}Don't worry about it. It was
very reassuring to have a first-class mage

00:01:36.012 --> 00:01:37.764
{\an8}traveling with me.

00:01:38.723 --> 00:01:41.518
But to think you're going to Ende…

00:01:42.185 --> 00:01:45.103
For people like me,
who stay in the town they're born in,

00:01:45.104 --> 00:01:46.773
it's hard to even imagine

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:50.485
how long the journey must be.

00:01:55.031 --> 00:01:56.324
I guess so.

00:01:59.327 --> 00:02:04.207
ORIGINAL STORY BY
KANEHITO YAMADA / TSUKASA ABE

00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:30.042
29 YEARS FROM THE DEATH OF HIMMEL THE HERO

00:03:30.043 --> 00:03:31.920
SAUM MARSHES IN THE NORTHERN LANDS

00:03:54.567 --> 00:03:57.362
I caught a fish.

00:03:58.279 --> 00:04:00.156
I'll add it to our breakfast then.

00:04:03.952 --> 00:04:06.329
I'll catch something bigger next time,
I swear.

00:04:07.372 --> 00:04:08.998
That's strange…

00:04:09.582 --> 00:04:11.918
I thought it would be around here.

00:04:12.835 --> 00:04:15.837
It's rare to see Frieren up so early.

00:04:15.838 --> 00:04:19.300
She said something caught her attention
and woke her up.

00:04:21.344 --> 00:04:23.680
- Did you make sure to praise her?
- Of course.

00:04:25.056 --> 00:04:25.932
Found it.

00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:31.646
This is a big one.

00:04:33.648 --> 00:04:35.232
What's that?

00:04:35.233 --> 00:04:37.860
- What a pretty stone.
- Here.

00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:44.117
What?

00:04:46.244 --> 00:04:47.745
My fire magic isn't working.

00:04:49.497 --> 00:04:51.499
This is a magic-nullifying crystal.

00:04:52.166 --> 00:04:55.211
It's a crystal that has
the power to nullify magic.

00:04:56.713 --> 00:05:00.924
With this level of purity, it can probably
nullify magic within a 3-meter radius.

00:05:00.925 --> 00:05:03.303
Stark, try walking away.

00:05:08.433 --> 00:05:09.349
It worked.

00:05:09.350 --> 00:05:11.893
It's very rare.

00:05:11.894 --> 00:05:15.480
Even ones that are pebble-sized
are easily worth a few gold coins.

00:05:15.481 --> 00:05:18.359
If you sell something this large,
you can buy a mansion.

00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:20.945
Wow.

00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:24.823
But if just having that near us

00:05:24.824 --> 00:05:27.785
prevents us from using magic,
we can't take it with us.

00:05:28.619 --> 00:05:30.370
It's dangerous to take on the road.

00:05:30.371 --> 00:05:32.206
That's the thing…

00:05:32.915 --> 00:05:35.293
Hurry up and throw that stone away.

00:05:36.252 --> 00:05:38.713
If a monster attacks us now,
we'll be done for.

00:05:39.505 --> 00:05:43.425
Before that, take a look at
this stone's interesting properties.

00:05:43.426 --> 00:05:45.385
It's really cool.

00:05:45.386 --> 00:05:48.639
When you fill it with a bunch of mana…

00:05:51.851 --> 00:05:53.770
it shines like crazy.

00:05:54.729 --> 00:05:55.854
It's blinding.

00:05:55.855 --> 00:05:57.356
Hurry up and toss that thing.

00:06:01.778 --> 00:06:03.196
It's still shining.

00:06:05.281 --> 00:06:07.825
We might be able to reach
the next town today.

00:06:08.910 --> 00:06:12.080
By the way,
are we near the Northern Plateau now?

00:06:12.580 --> 00:06:13.998
It's still a ways out.

00:06:14.916 --> 00:06:18.086
You have to pass a big forest
and a volcanic belt.

00:06:18.586 --> 00:06:23.090
A volcanic belt, huh?
That sounds kind of dangerous.

00:06:23.091 --> 00:06:24.925
It's not really.

00:06:24.926 --> 00:06:27.385
There haven't been any eruptions
for centuries.

00:06:27.386 --> 00:06:30.181
Right now, it's a relatively safe
hot spring location.

00:06:30.765 --> 00:06:31.891
Hot spring?

00:06:32.517 --> 00:06:35.727
A warm bath sounds kind of nice right now.

00:06:35.728 --> 00:06:38.940
We haven't enjoyed
something like that in a while.

00:06:43.736 --> 00:06:45.988
Hey, wait a second.

00:06:46.489 --> 00:06:48.908
The ground might be…

00:06:59.669 --> 00:07:00.877
Just as I thought…

00:07:00.878 --> 00:07:03.630
There was a hole underground.

00:07:03.631 --> 00:07:06.259
I hate how unstable the ground is
in wetlands.

00:07:07.051 --> 00:07:09.762
Wait… Mistress Frieren…

00:07:12.306 --> 00:07:14.100
Oops…

00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:25.027
No wonder we found
a magic-nullifying crystal on the surface.

00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:28.155
I've never seen an ore deposit
this massive before.

00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:29.740
Can you get off of me?

00:07:32.034 --> 00:07:34.871
This cave is practically
made of magic-nullifying crystals.

00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:38.498
If we take these with us,
we'll be billionaires.

00:07:38.499 --> 00:07:40.126
I don't think that's possible though.

00:07:42.253 --> 00:07:46.048
The magic-nullifying crystal
is some of the hardest existing matter.

00:07:46.716 --> 00:07:49.843
And unlike other matter,

00:07:49.844 --> 00:07:53.598
you cannot cut or process it
using magic either.

00:08:11.532 --> 00:08:14.535
It's not something mankind
can do anything about.

00:08:15.411 --> 00:08:19.290
{\an8}Anyway, it'll be impossible to climb
out of here, so let's find another exit.

00:08:28.966 --> 00:08:29.800
What is it?

00:08:30.885 --> 00:08:34.055
I'm counting on you, Stark.

00:08:34.805 --> 00:08:38.768
Since we can't use magic here,
we're just regular girls right now.

00:08:40.228 --> 00:08:41.312
"Girls"?

00:08:41.896 --> 00:08:45.942
Stark, I haven't forgotten about
the time you called me, "old hag."

00:08:46.901 --> 00:08:48.485
I'm sorry…

00:08:48.486 --> 00:08:50.196
She's still holding a grudge.

00:09:19.809 --> 00:09:23.604
Who knew we would end up
camping out at a place like this?

00:09:25.273 --> 00:09:28.484
What an incredibly large place…

00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:33.239
There were massive amounts
of animal bones too.

00:09:34.699 --> 00:09:36.366
Mistress Frieren

00:09:36.367 --> 00:09:39.328
said that a large monster
may be using this as a den.

00:09:41.330 --> 00:09:43.582
How can she sleep so soundly?

00:09:43.583 --> 00:09:45.293
She's so care-free.

00:09:47.795 --> 00:09:50.590
Mistress Frieren was having fun
even in a place like this.

00:09:52.466 --> 00:09:54.468
I am scared to death.

00:09:55.970 --> 00:09:57.930
I can't even do mana detection.

00:10:03.477 --> 00:10:05.896
I've never experienced
anything like this before.

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:10.985
I feel as though I was
thrown into darkness.

00:10:12.403 --> 00:10:13.321
Fern…

00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:20.202
A monster?

00:10:21.162 --> 00:10:23.331
Frieren, wake up! Run--

00:10:29.837 --> 00:10:31.254
It's a venomous apex dragon.

00:10:31.255 --> 00:10:32.173
Venomous…?

00:10:32.757 --> 00:10:34.675
It's not very compatible with you.

00:10:35.384 --> 00:10:36.760
You'll die from poisoning again.

00:10:36.761 --> 00:10:38.179
I never died!

00:10:38.846 --> 00:10:41.182
But… what am I supposed to do then?

00:10:41.807 --> 00:10:44.060
First of all,
I can't believe you were snoozing away.

00:10:44.727 --> 00:10:48.814
{\an8}- How can you be so--
- Because I've entrusted you with my life.

00:10:52.902 --> 00:10:56.822
I have done, ever since I recruited you
as our vanguard.

00:10:57.740 --> 00:11:00.993
That's how it should be,
or a party can't function.

00:11:03.371 --> 00:11:06.707
{\an8}I'm the kind of man who runs away
in times of need.

00:11:07.667 --> 00:11:10.794
Even now… I want to run away so badly.

00:11:10.795 --> 00:11:11.796
Yeah?

00:11:12.421 --> 00:11:14.215
Then let's run away together.

00:11:14.840 --> 00:11:18.052
Stark, Fern, close your eyes.

00:11:25.142 --> 00:11:25.976
Himmel,

00:11:26.727 --> 00:11:30.773
how could you say that
you've entrusted your life to me?

00:11:32.024 --> 00:11:35.361
That's not something
you should say so carelessly.

00:11:38.697 --> 00:11:41.367
I'm a man who abandoned his village
and ran away.

00:11:43.035 --> 00:11:43.953
Is that right?

00:11:45.037 --> 00:11:47.998
Well then, if you want to run away,
let's all run away together.

00:11:50.668 --> 00:11:53.379
We're a party, after all.

00:12:25.911 --> 00:12:27.746
Well then, shall we run?

00:12:31.876 --> 00:12:34.753
Why am I carrying the heavier one,
when I'm a priest?

00:12:35.671 --> 00:12:37.423
She says you stink of alcohol, Heiter.

00:12:57.234 --> 00:12:58.985
That was scary, huh?

00:12:58.986 --> 00:13:01.322
Running away together isn't so bad, right?

00:13:10.164 --> 00:13:11.707
Well then, let's get going.

00:13:17.254 --> 00:13:19.548
- Frieren.
- What?

00:13:20.132 --> 00:13:22.551
My legs gave out. I can't walk.

00:13:26.055 --> 00:13:28.014
29 YEARS FROM THE DEATH OF HIMMEL THE HERO

00:13:28.015 --> 00:13:29.975
THE GREAT SANFT FOREST
IN THE NORTHERN LANDS

00:13:31.185 --> 00:13:32.478
I wonder if this is

00:13:33.145 --> 00:13:34.939
enough ingredients for lunch?

00:13:36.899 --> 00:13:38.983
What? They're not here?

00:13:38.984 --> 00:13:41.487
Maybe I came back too early.

00:13:46.283 --> 00:13:48.953
All right,
maybe I'll go fish or something.

00:13:50.746 --> 00:13:52.831
I'll catch a big one today, for sure.

00:13:55.834 --> 00:13:57.169
It's cold.

00:13:58.963 --> 00:14:01.006
I can't wait until we find a hot spring.

00:14:12.351 --> 00:14:13.352
Nice and clean.

00:14:14.019 --> 00:14:16.063
The mirrored lotus bracelet.

00:14:16.564 --> 00:14:18.399
That's the one you got from Stark, right?

00:14:20.401 --> 00:14:22.861
The hair accessory that I got from you

00:14:22.862 --> 00:14:24.363
is nice and clean too.

00:14:24.989 --> 00:14:26.906
I noticed it with your staff too,

00:14:26.907 --> 00:14:29.952
but you look so happy
when you're cleaning your belongings.

00:14:30.619 --> 00:14:31.745
Is that right?

00:14:32.496 --> 00:14:34.081
See, you're smiling.

00:14:37.167 --> 00:14:39.879
Maybe it's because they are
gifts from people.

00:14:40.796 --> 00:14:42.547
I've lost everything,

00:14:42.548 --> 00:14:45.384
including my hometown,
to the war, after all.

00:14:46.093 --> 00:14:48.470
{\an8}So perhaps I'm happy to see my collection

00:14:48.971 --> 00:14:50.639
{\an8}of precious things grow.

00:14:51.724 --> 00:14:54.643
I'm glad I put a lot of thought into it.

00:14:55.352 --> 00:14:57.937
You were debating for a long time, huh?

00:14:57.938 --> 00:14:59.148
How do you know that?

00:15:04.028 --> 00:15:04.904
Pervert.

00:15:07.489 --> 00:15:09.366
I'm so sorry!

00:15:09.867 --> 00:15:12.536
I didn't know that you were bathing!

00:15:13.537 --> 00:15:15.497
It's not like I'm mad.

00:15:17.166 --> 00:15:18.792
There, all done.

00:15:35.100 --> 00:15:38.686
Hey Stark, I was thinking…

00:15:38.687 --> 00:15:39.521
What?

00:15:40.314 --> 00:15:43.191
Are things a little tense right now?

00:15:43.192 --> 00:15:44.526
Maybe.

00:15:45.235 --> 00:15:48.614
Frieren, you're able to pick up
on things like that now?

00:15:49.156 --> 00:15:50.532
I'm a little impressed.

00:15:51.158 --> 00:15:53.243
This happens every once in a while, huh?

00:15:53.744 --> 00:15:56.120
Are you two not compatible?

00:15:56.121 --> 00:15:58.374
I don't think that's the case.

00:15:59.667 --> 00:16:00.542
Stark.

00:16:02.461 --> 00:16:05.630
If you don't feel comfortable,
make sure you tell me.

00:16:05.631 --> 00:16:09.593
After all, I'm the one who
dragged you into our party.

00:16:10.594 --> 00:16:13.430
Hey, Frieren, I--

00:16:14.515 --> 00:16:15.933
It's a fork.

00:16:20.562 --> 00:16:22.314
This way leads to the Northern Plateau

00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:25.567
and that way leads to Neutral Harbor.

00:16:26.276 --> 00:16:27.403
Frieren.

00:16:27.903 --> 00:16:30.906
Is that perhaps an inn?

00:16:32.783 --> 00:16:35.785
I wouldn't be surprised,
since this is a main road.

00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:38.288
We might not have to camp outside tonight.

00:16:41.792 --> 00:16:43.711
Hey, if it isn't Frieren.

00:16:47.047 --> 00:16:49.341
I didn't expect to have a reunion so soon.

00:16:50.092 --> 00:16:54.346
Stark, thanks again for helping us
with the Fresser quest.

00:16:54.972 --> 00:16:57.850
Wirbel, you look well.

00:16:59.935 --> 00:17:02.730
In the end,
I have to take the sea route back.

00:17:03.605 --> 00:17:07.817
<i>Apparently, demons are wreaking havoc
in the far north again.</i>

00:17:07.818 --> 00:17:10.487
So I decided to rush back.

00:17:11.447 --> 00:17:14.158
We're traveling to the Imperial Capital's
port town together.

00:17:14.908 --> 00:17:17.869
He keeps complaining
about getting seasick.

00:17:17.870 --> 00:17:21.748
You're an old man already, aren't you?
Come on.

00:17:21.749 --> 00:17:23.499
Listen.

00:17:23.500 --> 00:17:26.836
I'll have you know that
I'm not an old man yet.

00:17:26.837 --> 00:17:29.672
I was in my twenties until just recently.

00:17:29.673 --> 00:17:32.968
I know another old man
who used to say that.

00:17:34.928 --> 00:17:36.180
Say, Stark.

00:17:36.805 --> 00:17:39.183
Did you give my offer any thought?

00:17:39.808 --> 00:17:41.310
Offer?

00:17:43.312 --> 00:17:46.315
The war on the northern front
is not looking good.

00:17:47.066 --> 00:17:49.818
We have an overwhelming shortage
of vanguards.

00:17:51.278 --> 00:17:55.782
I don't want to force you.
But it'd be great if you can support us

00:17:55.783 --> 00:17:58.744
for two to three years,
until the battlefront is stabilized.

00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:03.164
I already told you, remember?

00:18:03.165 --> 00:18:05.709
I'm the vanguard for this party.

00:18:06.293 --> 00:18:09.463
Okay, but I'm the type
who doesn't know when to give up.

00:18:09.963 --> 00:18:13.342
I will do anything
for the sake of protecting the far north.

00:18:15.886 --> 00:18:18.722
Frieren, will you allow me to woo him?

00:18:20.057 --> 00:18:21.892
- Um--
- Do whatever you like.

00:18:25.521 --> 00:18:26.730
Mistress Frieren…

00:18:27.564 --> 00:18:30.316
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:18:30.317 --> 00:18:32.902
Stark, you seriously need to…

00:18:32.903 --> 00:18:34.738
He looks like he's having fun.

00:18:35.948 --> 00:18:38.157
Maybe our party

00:18:38.158 --> 00:18:41.620
was a little suffocating for Stark.

00:18:42.579 --> 00:18:44.873
- I hear Wirbel is treating us today?
- What?

00:18:53.715 --> 00:18:55.884
Um… Master Stark…

00:18:56.760 --> 00:18:59.138
If you're wondering about Wirbel,
I turned him down.

00:19:02.724 --> 00:19:05.435
Are you sure you're okay with that?

00:19:06.436 --> 00:19:09.898
Fern, why do you think I'm in this party?

00:19:12.693 --> 00:19:15.195
When I first met you guys,

00:19:16.655 --> 00:19:19.032
I was at my limit, to be honest.

00:19:20.033 --> 00:19:22.076
<i>I was on the verge of leaving</i>

00:19:22.077 --> 00:19:24.538
<i>everything behind
and abandoning the village.</i>

00:19:25.789 --> 00:19:27.040
<i>I'm the worst, right?</i>

00:19:28.083 --> 00:19:29.750
Frieren said that

00:19:29.751 --> 00:19:33.629
she "dragged me into the party."

00:19:33.630 --> 00:19:34.756
But that's not true.

00:19:40.429 --> 00:19:41.722
I don't think

00:19:42.598 --> 00:19:44.099
you will run away.

00:19:48.770 --> 00:19:52.191
It's because you encouraged me that night,

00:19:52.691 --> 00:19:56.069
that I felt like traveling with you guys
and joined the party.

00:19:57.988 --> 00:20:00.407
You probably have no clue, Fern,

00:20:01.116 --> 00:20:04.119
but Frieren isn't the only one
who has brought

00:20:05.037 --> 00:20:07.122
a coward like me this far.

00:20:11.210 --> 00:20:13.378
I won't be going anywhere.

00:20:16.965 --> 00:20:19.134
So be more kind to me.

00:20:21.511 --> 00:20:22.638
Understood.

00:20:23.305 --> 00:20:25.766
Come here, then.
I will give you lots of pets.

00:20:26.642 --> 00:20:28.435
What are you scheming? I'm scared!

00:20:29.102 --> 00:20:31.146
<i>What a pain…</i>

00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:19.820
I guess I couldn't persuade you
in the end.

00:21:20.529 --> 00:21:23.699
By the way,
you three don't plan on traveling by boat?

00:21:24.449 --> 00:21:26.952
Traveling by sea will cost
an absurd amount of money.

00:21:28.161 --> 00:21:29.412
Plus…

00:21:29.413 --> 00:21:30.579
After all,

00:21:30.580 --> 00:21:33.709
our masters took
the Northern Plateau route as well.

00:21:36.712 --> 00:21:38.213
We'll end up accepting strange requests

00:21:39.006 --> 00:21:40.716
and get caught up in trouble

00:21:41.383 --> 00:21:43.260
and keep making detours, though.

00:21:46.930 --> 00:21:50.475
I guess you guys have
your own adventures to enjoy.

00:21:51.476 --> 00:21:54.813
Well, whatever. You're coming
to the far north eventually, anyway.

00:21:55.814 --> 00:21:58.317
When you do, we'll meet again.

00:22:04.197 --> 00:22:05.699
Well then, let's get going.

00:23:51.096 --> 00:23:52.972
<i>- That sounds like an exaggeration.
- What a tyrant.</i>

00:23:52.973 --> 00:23:54.974
<i>- He likes accepting troublesome requests.
- You don't waste time. I like that.</i>

00:23:54.975 --> 00:23:57.351
<i>- She looks very unhappy.
- I will die before I can</i>

00:23:57.352 --> 00:23:59.687
<i>- fulfill my goal.
- But we were able to kill a demon.</i>

00:23:59.688 --> 00:24:00.855
<i>He's the Hero of the South.</i>

00:24:00.856 --> 00:24:01.898
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

00:24:02.305 --> 00:25:02.682
